cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep learning framework for traffic forecasting, which involves the use of capsule networks and nested LSTM models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers topics related to the development and analysis of machine learning algorithms. The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques for traffic forecasting, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The use of capsule networks suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision), which covers topics related to image and video analysis. The paper also involves the use of spatiotemporal data, which suggests that it may belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which cover topics related to network analysis and neural networks, respectively.
